title: Onsite Rental's IPO pulled on bookbuild day
text:
Equipment rental business Onsite Rental's shareholders have pulled the company's proposed initial public offering.

Onsite Rental's brokers were scheduled to run a bookbuild to collect bids for the proposed $238.9 million to $252.8 million equity raising on Monday.

However, Onsite Rental's owners met prior to the bookbuild and opted to cancel the float.

The owners cited poor IPO market conditions for the decision.

It's the sixth $150 million-plus proposed Australian IPO to be cancelled in the past two weeks. Others include Latitude Financial Group, PropertyGuru, Education Centres of Australia, Retail Zoo and MPC Kinetic.
description: Equipment rental business Onsite Rentals' shareholders have pulled the company's proposed initial public offering.
